Vonage Holdings Corp. (NYSE:VG) Receives An Update From Brokers


 By Ashley Brown /  in  Stocks /  on  Thursday, 20 Jul 2017 11:38 AM  / 0 Comments




Analysts reviewing Vonage Holdings Corp. have recently updated their recommended buy/sell ratings and price targets on the stock.  			         



Based on their most recently released notes to investors, 6 analysts have a rating of “buy”, 4 analysts “outperform”, 1 analysts “hold”, 0 analysts “underperform” and 0 analysts “sell”.
Ratings and price target breakdown:
 05/23/2017 – Vonage Holdings Corp. had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at William Blair.
 01/11/2017 – Vonage Holdings Corp. had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at Needham & Company. They now have a USD 9 price target on the stock.
 09/13/2016 – Robert W. Baird began new coverage on Vonage Holdings Corp. giving the company a “” rating. They now have a USD 8 price target on the stock.
 09/12/2016 – Vonage Holdings Corp. had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at Dougherty & Co. They now have a USD 9 price target on the stock.
 08/01/2016 – Vonage Holdings Corp. had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at FBN Securities.
 06/30/2016 – Vonage Holdings Corp. had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at Citigroup. They now have a USD 8 price target on the stock.
 03/08/2016 – Summit Research began new coverage on Vonage Holdings Corp. giving the company a “” rating. They now have a USD 6 price target on the stock.
 02/12/2016 – Vonage Holdings Corp. had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at Oppenheimer. They now have a USD 6.5 price target on the stock.
 11/04/2015 – Vonage Holdings Corp. had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at Canaccord Genuity.
 08/21/2015 – Vonage Holdings Corp. had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at Northland Securities. They now have a USD 7.55 price target on the stock.
 05/11/2015 – Vonage Holdings Corp. was upgraded to “” by analysts at Zacks. They now have a USD 5 price target on the stock.
 03/07/2014 – Vonage Holdings Corp. was upgraded to “” by analysts at EVA Dimensions.
 02/21/2014 – Vonage Holdings Corp. was upgraded to “” by analysts at Jefferson Research.
 01/22/2014 – Craig-Hallum began new coverage on Vonage Holdings Corp. giving the company a “” rating. They now have a USD 7 price target on the stock.
 11/15/2013 – National Alliance Securities began new coverage on Vonage Holdings Corp. giving the company a “” rating. They now have a USD 4.1 price target on the stock.
Vonage Holdings Corp. has a 50 day moving average of 6.73 and a 200 day moving average of 6.65. The stock’s market capitalization is 1.45B, it has a 52-week low of 5.43 and a 52-week high of 7.88. 
The share price of the company (NYSE:VG) was up +0.92%, with a high of 6.61 during the day and the volume of Vonage Holdings Corp. shares traded was 1515857.  



Vonage Holdings Corp. is a provider of cloud communications services for businesses and consumers, and consumer and communication solutions across multiple devices. The Company operates through two segments: Business and Consumer. For business services customers, the Company provides cloud-based unified communications as a service (UCaaS) solutions, consisting of integrated voice, text, video, data, collaboration, and mobile applications over its scalable session initiation protocol (SIP) based voice over Internet protocol (VoIP) network. It serves a range of the business market, including the small and medium business (SMB), mid-market and enterprise segments. Through its cloud-based middleware solution, gUnify, the Company provides customers the ability to integrate its cloud communications platform with various cloud-based productivity and customer relationship management (CRM) solutions, including Google’s G Suite, Zendesk, Salesforce’s Sales Cloud, Oracle and Clio.


